      "## Practical Tips for Your Greece Adventure",
      "To enjoy the Greek islands without the intense summer heat and crowds, aim to visit in May-June or September-October. If you are traveling in July and August, pack lightweight resort wear, swimwear, a hat, and plenty of sunscreen. Comfortable sandals or walking shoes are essential for walking up the steps of the Acropolis or navigating the steep pathways of Santorini's villages. Savoring local taverna dishes is a highlight, and tipping is appreciated but not mandatory. Credit cards are widely accepted, but having a few Euros cash is helpful for small island shops.",
