      "## Practical Tips for Your Jordan Adventure",
      "The ideal months to visit Jordan are during the spring (March to May) or autumn (September to November) when temperatures are moderate. If you plan to float in the Dead Sea, remember to pack swimwear, water shoes to protect your feet from salt crystals, and avoid shaving beforehand to prevent stinging. Wadi Rum deserts can get surprisingly cold at night, so bring warm layers even in summer. Sturdy hiking shoes are highly recommended for walking the cobblestone trails of Petra. Respect local customs by dressing modestly, and always ask for permission before taking photos of local Bedouins. Drink bottled water and keep cash on hand for souvenirs.",
